<a name="I">

<H1>I
</H1>


<P>
<A name="index_39_11"></A> The <B>\I</B> tag marks text to be formatted <I><B>i</B>talic</I>.
</P>


<P>
<B>Syntax</B>
</P>


<P>
\I&lt;body&gt;
</P>


<P>
<B>Options</B>
</P>


<P>
No options are allowed. Using options will cause a syntax error.
</P>


<P>
<B>Body</B>
</P>


<P>
The body is the string to be formatted.
</P>


<P>
<B>Notes</B>
</P>


<P>
<B>\I</B> is part of the <I>basic tag set</I> supported by <I>all</I> PerlPoint translators.
</P>


<P>
<B>Example</B>
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
  This text is \I&lt;formatted&gt;.
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


<P>
produces
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
  This text is <I>formatted</I>.
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


<P>
<B>See also</B>
</P>


<P>
More basic set tags: <B>\B</B>, <B>\C</B>, <B>\IMAGE</B> and <B>\READY</B>.
</P>


<P>

</P>
